    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <summary>Cross-platform desktop system metrics monitor (CPU / RAM / GPU / processes)</summary>
    <description>
CoreMetrics is a small C++23 system monitor built directly on raw SDL3 pixel surfaces.
It shows live CPU, RAM, GPU, and per-process resource usage with an optional rolling
sparklines view and an htop-style kill flow on the Processes tab.

No Qt, no Electron, no JavaScript runtime. Every widget is hand-rasterized by code in
the upstream repository. Three native metrics backends (Linux /proc, macOS Mach + IOKit,
Windows PDH) are selected at compile time so the same source tree builds the same UI
on each platform.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/sviatil0/coremetrics/releases/tag/v0.1.1</releaseNotes>
    <tags>system monitor cpu ram gpu process htop sdl3 native cross-platform</tags>
